@node INTRODUCTION "Introduction"
@{b}WW-Circles.rexx @{ub}

   This program creates circles with the same centre in Wordworth. You can choose the page of the
   document, the radius of the largest and of the smallest circle, and whether you want to have
   a tiny little circle indicating the centre of all these circles. All measures are in cm.

   If you want to have measures in inch, do the following:
   1. Load WW-Circles.rexx with a text editor (Wordworth will do, too)
   2. Change cm into in wherever you find it (be sure you don't make a blank space where there is
      none, or leave one out - Wordworth is very rigorous in that respect!)
      You can do that with the "find-replace"-option.
   3. Save it again. If you have used WW or another word processor, save it as ASCII.

@endnode
@node INSTALLATION "Installation"

@{b}Installation@{ub}

   Copy "WW-Circles.rexx" in the drawer WWRexx. Then you go to "ARexx-Macro" in
   the Wordworth-menu "Extras", click on "new" and then on "WW-Circles.rexx", of course.
   Now you can start it by another double-click.


@endnode
@node PROBLEMS "Problems"

@{b}Problems@{ub}

   In WW 5, the circles are not in the right place. You have to select the "Info"-window for
   each of them and close it again. Sorry, this is not my fault. It cost me some hours to
   find that out. :-|

@endnode
